                    "name": "Adaptation Aura",
                    "ability_type": "offensive",
                    "traits": [
                        {
                            "name": "Aura",
                            "type": "trait",
                            "alternate_link": {
                                "type": "alternate_link",
                                "game-obj": "Traits",
                                "aonid": 206,
                                "alternate_type": "legacy"
                            },
                            "edition": "remastered",
                            "sources": [
                                {
                                    "type": "source",
                                    "name": "Player Core",
                                    "link": {
                                        "type": "link",
                                        "name": "Player Core pg. 453",
                                        "alt": "Player Core pg. 453",
                                        "game-obj": "Sources",
                                        "aonid": 216
                                    },
                                    "page": 453,
                                    "errata": {
                                        "type": "link",
                                        "name": "2.0",
                                        "alt": "2.0",
                                        "game-obj": "Sources",
                                        "aonid": 216
                                    }
                                }
                            ],
                            "game-obj": "Traits",
                            "game-id": "5315505cfd3f3ba2685e9747898193b2",
                            "text": "An aura is an emanation that continually ebbs out from you, affecting creatures within a certain radius. Aura can also refer to the magical signature of an item.",
                            "schema_version": 1.1
                        }
                    ],
                    "text": "10 feet. The vehicle has a warding aura that protects its passengers. Creatures and objects in the aura gain resistance 10 to acid, cold, electricity, fire, force, sonic, vitality, and void damage. They are also protected from severe cold, severe heat, extreme cold, and extreme heat . The aura also provides breathable air for all passengers, though this air can still become filled with smoke and similar substances.",
                    "links": [
                        {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "severe cold, severe heat, extreme cold, and extreme heat",
                            "alt": "severe cold, severe heat, extreme cold, and extreme heat",
                            "game-obj": "Rules",
                            "aonid": 642
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "type": "stat_block_section",
                    "subtype": "ability",
                    "name": "Journey the Planes",
                    "ability_type": "offensive",
                    "text": "10 minutes; The pilot locks onto a plane, using one of the vehicle's planar keys as a focus. A canal of planar energy from the destination plane appears ahead of the ship. The pilot spends 10 minutes navigating the passage, then attempts a piloting check (typically DC 34). On a success, the vehicle casts  *interplanar teleport* , transporting itself and all passengers and cargo to the destination plane as it reaches the terminus of the canal. The pilot is considered the target of the spell for the purposes of determining the location at which the vehicle arrives on the plane. The skiff can't  *interplanar teleport* again for 8 hours.",
                    "links": [
                        {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "interplanar teleport",
                            "alt": "interplanar teleport",
                            "game-obj": "Spells",
                            "aonid": 222
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "type": "stat_block_section",
                    "subtype": "ability",
                    "name": "Planar Evacuation",
                    "ability_type": "offensive",
                    "traits": [
                        {
                            "name": "Move",
                            "type": "trait",
                            "alternate_link": {
                                "type": "alternate_link",
                                "game-obj": "Traits",
                                "aonid": 114,
                                "alternate_type": "legacy"
                            },
                            "edition": "remastered",
                            "sources": [
                                {
                                    "type": "source",
                                    "name": "Player Core",
                                    "link": {
                                        "type": "link",
                                        "name": "Player Core pg. 458",
                                        "alt": "Player Core pg. 458",
                                        "game-obj": "Sources",
                                        "aonid": 216
                                    },
                                    "page": 458,
                                    "errata": {
                                        "type": "link",
                                        "name": "2.0",
                                        "alt": "2.0",
                                        "game-obj": "Sources",
                                        "aonid": 216
                                    }
                                }
                            ],
                            "game-obj": "Traits",
                            "game-id": "43fcaf1d1171371e823b967f56d0b7a2",
                            "text": "An action with this trait involves moving from one space to another.",
                            "schema_version": 1.1
                        },
                        {
                            "name": "Reckless",
                            "type": "trait",
                            "alternate_link": {
                                "type": "alternate_link",
                                "game-obj": "Traits",
                                "aonid": 285,
                                "alternate_type": "legacy"
                            },
                            "edition": "remastered",
                            "sources": [
                                {
                                    "type": "source",
                                    "name": "GM Core",
                                    "link": {
                                        "type": "link",
                                        "name": "GM Core pg. 212",
                                        "alt": "GM Core pg. 212",
                                        "game-obj": "Sources",
                                        "aonid": 218
                                    },
                                    "page": 212,
                                    "errata": {
                                        "type": "link",
                                        "name": "2.0",
                                        "alt": "2.0",
                                        "game-obj": "Sources",
                                        "aonid": 218
                                    }
                                }
                            ],
                            "game-obj": "Traits",
                            "game-id": "c0a85803365a7164141fab4b4a1e7ba6",
                            "text": "Actions that have the reckless trait push the pilot and the vehicle beyond the normal parameters for safe operation, and the pilot risks losing control of the vehicle. When performing a reckless action, the pilot must first attempt an appropriate piloting check to keep control of the vehicle, with the following effects. Resolve this piloting check before resolving the action itself.  \n  \n__Success__ The action occurs as described.   \n__Failure__ The vehicle moves its Speed in a straight line along its most recent heading, drifting up to 45 degrees at the GM\u2019s discretion, and becomes uncontrolled.",
                            "schema_version": 1.1
                        }
                    ],
                    "text": "The pilot overcharges one of the vehicle's planar keys, forcing an emergency transport of the ship. The pilot attempts a DC 44 piloting check. On a success, the vehicle casts  *interplanar teleport* as noted in Journey the Planes. (The pilot can't succeed on the check if the vessel is unable to  *interplanar teleport* .) This process severely taxes the vehicle, and it can't  *interplanar teleport* again for 1d4 days.",
                    "action_type": {
                        "type": "stat_block_section",
                        "subtype": "action_type",
                        "name": "Three Actions"
                    }
                }
            ]
